about.summary: Uses the node library 'is-my-json-valid' or 'ajv' to validate 'JSON' against a 'JSON' schema.  Drafts 04, 06 and 07 of 'JSON' schema are supported.

name: r-jsonvalidate
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '1.1.0' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-jsonvalidate
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/jsonvalidate_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/jsonvalidate/jsonvalidate_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 5db7d1073a1fdee71f55e054220d234774a70da1149ef8d6af8714b5e7a6b3ef

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 2
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-v8
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-v8

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('jsonvalidate')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('jsonvalidate')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/ropensci/jsonvalidate
  license: MIT
  summary: Uses the node library 'is-my-json-valid' or 'ajv' to validate 'JSON' against a 'JSON'
    schema.  Drafts 04, 06 and 07 of 'JSON' schema are supported.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - xhochy
